# 5. Firmware Features

The firmware includes the following features.

## Automatic Irrigation

The ESP32 reads soil moisture continuously.

Logic:

* If soil value exceeds threshold → irrigation ON
* Otherwise → irrigation OFF

Threshold used:

```cpp
const int DRY_THRESHOLD = 2000;
```

---

## Manual Override

A physical push button toggles manual mode.

Manual mode behavior:

* Press button once → enable manual mode
* Press again → toggle valve state

This allows testing without changing soil conditions.

---

## Serial Commands

Three serial commands are supported:

### STATUS

Displays:

* Soil moisture percentage
* Pump/valve state
* Current mode

Example output:

```text
=== STATUS ===
Soil Moisture %: 51
Pump: ON
Mode: AUTO
```

### FORCE_ON

Forces valve ON.

### FORCE_OFF

Forces valve OFF.

---

## Web Server Control

ESP32 runs a local HTTP server on port 80.

Available endpoints:

### Turn ON

```text
/on
```

### Turn OFF

```text
/off
```

### Check Status

```text
/status
```

This allows browser-based control.

---

## Telemetry Upload

The firmware uploads soil moisture data to Zelbytes cloud.

Uploaded JSON:

```json
{
  "soil_moisture_pct": 52
}
```

Telemetry interval:

* Every 3 seconds

API headers:

* Content-Type: application/json
* X-Iot-Lab-Key: authentication key

