# 6. Calibration Methodology

Calibration was performed by testing the sensor in two conditions.

## Dry Soil Test

Sensor inserted in relatively dry soil.

Observed reading:

```text
1500
```

---

## Wet Soil Test

Sensor inserted in wet soil.

Observed reading:

```text
2069
```

---

## Threshold Selection

Chosen threshold:

```text
2000
```

Decision:

* Above 2000 → dry enough to irrigate
* Below 2000 → sufficient moisture

### Observation

This sensor showed inverted behavior compared to many common soil sensors, where wet readings are usually lower than dry readings. Calibration confirmed the sensor behavior for this setup.

